Monitoring package release depend on the infrastructure used.
On sourceforge, that's easy to monitor a package release.
You need to be logged and use links supplied, this will update the Monitoring
section of your profile.

With many packages, an annouce is send from http://freshmeat.net.
It is sometime forgotted and freshmeat page is often late.

Some GNU packages use a common info-gnu mailing list (see at the bottom)
On other cases, an announce mailing list may be available.
Announce list should be not verbose.
I (Gilles) didn't find the proper way for cpan packages announces

